# 🚀 AWS CI/CD Pipeline - Todo App Deployment

## 📖 Overview

This project demonstrates how to automate the deployment of a Todo Application using **AWS CI/CD services**.

Whenever code is pushed to GitHub, the pipeline automatically builds, stores the build artifacts, and deploys the application to an Amazon EC2 instance.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture

```
GitHub
   │
   ▼
AWS CodePipeline
   │
   ├── Source Stage (Fetch Code)
   │
   ├── Build Stage (AWS CodeBuild)
   │
   ├── Artifact Store (Amazon S3)
   │
   └── Deploy Stage (AWS CodeDeploy)
   │
   ▼
Amazon EC2
```

---

## 🛠️ AWS Services Used

- GitHub
- AWS CodePipeline
- AWS CodeBuild
- Amazon S3
- AWS CodeDeploy
- Amazon EC2
- Amazon CloudWatch

---

## 🔄 Pipeline Flow

1. Developer pushes code to GitHub.
2. AWS CodePipeline detects the changes.
3. AWS CodeBuild builds the application and runs the build commands.
4. The build artifacts are stored in Amazon S3.
5. AWS CodeDeploy deploys the application to the EC2 instance.
6. The application is live and ready to use.
7. Amazon CloudWatch monitors logs and application health.

