## ✅ Prerequisites

Before running this project, make sure you have:

- AWS Account
- GitHub Repository
- EC2 Instance
- CodeDeploy Agent installed on EC2
- IAM Roles configured
- AWS CLI installed

---

## ▶️ How to Use

### Step 1

Create a GitHub repository and push your application code.

### Step 2

Create an S3 bucket to store build artifacts.

### Step 3

Create a CodeBuild project.

### Step 4

Create a CodeDeploy application and deployment group.

### Step 5

Create a CodePipeline and connect all stages.

### Step 6

Push new code to GitHub.

The pipeline will automatically build and deploy the application to EC2.

